ChatMeet is committed to maintaining a safe environment for all users. We strictly prohibit any form of child sexual abuse material (CSAM) or exploitation content on our platform.

Our Standards
Zero Tolerance: We do not permit, promote, or distribute child sexual abuse material (CSAM) or any content that exploits or endangers children.

Adult‑Only Use: StrangerChat is intended for adults (18+) only. Minors are not allowed to use the app.

Content Monitoring: Any reports of CSAM or exploitation are taken seriously. We will act promptly to remove such content and disable offending accounts.

Reporting to Authorities: We cooperate fully with law enforcement and relevant child protection organizations when CSAM or exploitation is detected or reported.

User Responsibility: Users must not share, request, or encourage any content that involves child sexual abuse or exploitation. Violations will result in immediate account termination and reporting.

Enforcement
We reserve the right to suspend or permanently ban any user who violates this policy. All detected or reported CSAE content will be escalated to appropriate authorities in compliance with applicable laws.

Commitment
By using ChatMeet, you agree to uphold these standards and understand that CSAE content is strictly forbidden. Our priority is to provide a safe, respectful, and lawful environment for all users.
